An act for the encouraging & increasing of shipping and navigation England and Wales. Sovereign (1660-1685 : Charles II) England and Wales. Parliament.
[2], 21, [1] p.
Printed by John Bill and Christopher Barker, Printers to the Kings most Excellent Majesty, [London : 1660]
Caption title. Imprint from general title page. At head of caption: Anno XII. Caroli II. Regis. Signatures: A-F² . Last word of first line of text: 'shipping'; first word of line below initial: 'strength'; last word of last full line of text of first page: 'or'. Also includes: An act to prevent frauds and concealments of His Majesties customs and subsidies. Issued separately with a general title page: 'Anno Regni Caroli II. Regis Angliæ, Scotiæ, Franciæ, & Hiberniæ, duodecimo. At the Parliament begun at VVestminster, the five and twentieth day of April, an. Dom. 1660.'. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Sept 18". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
